[thinking] I’m looking at how the TCK test runs. It seems like the `test` command triggers the `tckTest`, which then executes `nativeTest`. The `nativeTest` likely just runs the already compiled native code with existing metadata. I might consider that dynamic coverage could come from the JVM earlier in the process. To ensure proper coverage, the test must pass on the native side, and I could conditionally run a hack just on the JVM while using an existing assertion for native.
[thinking] 
