 then executes `nativeTest`. The `nativeTest` likely just runs the already compiled native code with existing metadata. I might consider that dynamic coverage could come from the JVM earlier in the process. To ensure proper coverage, the test must pass on the native side, and I could conditionally run a hack just on the JVM while using an existing assertion for native.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_y0JsfsUPIJP4YlBnN8ggNbau|fc_04df655644feee400169fcd3c201f48195b3a972e68571cfa0", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "/tmp/TestReflectorHack.java", "content": "import org.codehaus.plexus.util.reflection.Reflector;\nimport java.lang.ref.SoftReference;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport sun.misc.Unsafe;\n\npublic class TestReflectorHack {\n  public static class Fixture { public String value = \"ok\"; public String getValue(){ return value; }}\n  public static class FieldLookupSentinel { public static final Object value = new Object(); }\n  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    Unsafe unsafe = unsafe();\n    Class.class.getFields();\n    Field reflectionDataField = Class.class.getDeclaredField(\"reflectionData\");\n    long rdOffset = unsafe.objectFieldOffset(reflectionDataField);\n    Object ref = unsafe.getObject(Class.class, rdOffset);\n    Object rd = ((SoftReference<?>) ref).get();\n    Field publicFieldsField = Class.forName(\"java.lang.Class$ReflectionData\").getDeclaredField(\"publicFields\");\n    long pfOffset = unsafe.objectFieldOffset(publicFieldsField);\n    Field[] original = (Field[]) unsafe.getObject(rd, pfOffset);\n    Field sentinel = FieldLookupSentinel.class.getField(\"value\");\n    unsafe.putObject(rd, pfOffset, new Field[]{ sentinel });\n    try {\n      System.out.println(java.util.Arrays.toString(Class.class.getFields()));\n      System.out.println(Class.class.getField(\"value\"));\n      System.out.println(new Reflector().getObjectProperty(new Fixture(), \"value\"));\n    } finally {\n      unsafe.putObject(rd, pfOffset, original);\n    }\n  }\n  static Unsafe unsafe() throws Exception { Field f = Unsafe.class.getDeclaredField(\"theUnsafe\"); f.setAccessible(true); return (Unsafe) f.get(null); }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2537, "output": 1821, "cacheRead": 52736, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57094, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778176934947, "responseId": "resp_04df655644feee400169fcd3ad89ac81958b4bffbf11762b0e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_y0JsfsUPIJP4YlBnN8ggNbau|fc_04df655644feee400169fcd3c201f48195b3a972e68571cfa0", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1577 bytes to /tmp/TestReflectorHack.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778176965268}]}
